  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations:\n\n1. United States Approach\n- Comprehensive Bank Secrecy Act\n- Strong federal criminal penalties\n- Mandatory reporting requirements\n- Aggressive prosecution strategies\n- Extensive regulatory framework\n\n2. European Union Approach\n- Unified Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Coordinated cross-border enforcement\n- Emphasis on financial institution compliance\n- Enhanced customer due diligence requirements\n- More harmonized legal standards\n\n3. Swiss Model\n- Traditionally strict banking secrecy laws\n- Increasing international cooperation\n- Sophisticated financial monitoring systems\n- Complex identification protocols\n- Gradual movement towards transparency\n\n4. UK Approach\n- Sophisticated financial intelligence unit\n- Risk-based regulatory framework\n- Strong international collaboration\n- Advanced technological monitoring\n- Comprehensive legislative mechanisms\n\n5. Asian Variations\n- China: Centralized control\n- Singapore: Strict regulatory environment\n- Japan: Detailed compliance frameworks\n- Emerging economies: Developing legal infrastructures\n\nKey comparative elements:\n- Regulatory intensity\n- Criminal prosecution approaches\n- International cooperation levels\n- Technological implementation\n- Financial sector engagement\n\nThis overview represents general trends, recognizing significant nuanced variations between jurisdictions.",
